## 8. Logging Rules

### Always Use Winston — Never console.*

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — server side
import { logger } from '../lib/logger';
logger.info('Goal created', { userId, goalId: goal.id });
logger.warn('Rate limit approached', { userId, endpoint: '/analysis' });
logger.error('Market data failed', { ticker, error: err.message });

// ✅ CORRECT — frontend (only in development)
if (import.meta.env.DEV) {
  console.error('WebSocket error:', err);
}

// ❌ WRONG — anywhere in server code
console.log('Goal created');
console.error(err);
console.warn('something happened');
```

