## 10. i18n Rules

All user-facing text must use the translation system. No exceptions.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
const { t } = useTranslation('common');
<h1>{t('dashboard.title')}</h1>
<p>{t('errors.loadFailed')}</p>
<button>{t('common.save')}</button>
toast.error(t('goals.limitReached'));

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded Arabic or English text
<h1>لوحة التحكم</h1>
<h1>Dashboard</h1>
toast.error('لقد وصلت للحد الأقصى من الأهداف');
```

Translation keys must exist in both:
- `public/locales/ar/common.json`
- `public/locales/en/common.json`

