## 11. State Management Rules

### Use Zustand for Global State — useContext Only for Theme/Locale

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — global auth state via Zustand
const { user, accessToken, logout } = useAuthStore();
const user = useAuthStore((s) => s.user);            // selector for performance
const logout = useAuthStore((s) => s.logout);        // single value selector

// ✅ CORRECT — local component state via useState
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [search, setSearch] = useState('');

// ❌ WRONG — prop drilling auth through multiple levels
<App user={user} accessToken={accessToken}>
  <Sidebar user={user}>
    <ProfileMenu user={user} onLogout={logout} />
  </Sidebar>
</App>
```

### Avoid Prop Drilling Beyond 1 Level

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — consume directly from store
function ProfileMenu() {
  const { user, logout } = useAuthStore(); // consume directly
  return <button onClick={logout}>{user?.fullName}</button>;
}

// ❌ WRONG — passed through 3 levels
<App onLogout={logout}>
  <Header onLogout={onLogout}>
    <ProfileMenu onLogout={onLogout} />
  </Header>
</App>
```

